	"order": 1,
	"title": "Le passé composé (avoir) — Talking about the past",
	"objective": "Recount recent past events using the passé composé with avoir (A2: can describe past activities and personal experiences).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: “have + done” = avoir + past participle",
		"body": "The passé composé is built like the English present perfect: **avoir** (present) + a **past participle**. Regular -er verbs form their participle in **-é**: manger → **mangé**, visiter → **visité**. So *j'ai mangé* = “I ate / I have eaten”. Hindi marks the past with separate forms (मैंने खाया), so focus on the two-part French structure: helper verb + participle."
	},
